---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About - Dashboard Demo" description="A lightweight, no-auth dashboard demo built with Astro.">
  <section class="py-20">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        <h1 class="text-gray-900 mb-6">About Dashboard Demo</h1>
        
        <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
          <p class="text-xl text-gray-600 mb-8">
            Dashboard Demo is a lightweight static site: a landing page plus a KPI dashboard you can share publicly.
            It's designed for prototypes and demos that don't need user authentication or a backend.
          </p>
          
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-4">Technology Stack</h2>
          <ul class="space-y-3 text-gray-600">
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-primary-600 font-semibold">Astro 5</span>
              <span>- Static site generation with island architecture</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-primary-600 font-semibold">Tailwind CSS</span>
              <span>- Utility-first CSS framework for rapid styling</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-primary-600 font-semibold">React</span>
              <span>- Optional interactive widgets via islands</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-primary-600 font-semibold">TypeScript</span>
              <span>- Type safety throughout the project</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
          
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-4">Deployment</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">
            This site deploys as a single nginx container serving static files. The build process:
          </p>
          <ol class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-600 ml-4">
            <li>Runs <code class="bg-gray-100 px-2 py-1 rounded">npm run build</code> to generate static files</li>
            <li>Packages files into an nginx container</li>
            <li>Pushes to the container registry</li>
            <li>ArgoCD deploys to Kubernetes</li>
          </ol>
          
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-4">When to Use This</h2>
          <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8 mt-6">
            <div class="bg-green-50 rounded-lg p-6">
              <h3 class="font-semibold text-green-900 mb-3">Good For</h3>
              <ul class="space-y-2 text-green-800 text-sm">
                <li>Public demo dashboards</li>
                <li>Sales walkthroughs</li>
                <li>UI prototypes and iterations</li>
                <li>Static marketing + demo pages</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-red-50 rounded-lg p-6">
              <h3 class="font-semibold text-red-900 mb-3">Not For</h3>
              <ul class="space-y-2 text-red-800 text-sm">
                <li>User authentication</li>
                <li>Database-backed apps</li>
                <li>Payment processing</li>
                <li>Real-time features</li>
                <li>Full SaaS applications</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
          <p class="text-gray-600 mt-6">
            If you need authentication, a database, or billing, this repo is best treated as a UI reference and replaced with a full app.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
